 ProxyNetTest 📶  
Flutter Internet Speed & Network Quality Analyzer
ProxyNetTest is a Flutter-based mobile application designed to measure real-world internet performance, including download speed, upload speed, ping, and TCP latency. It also provides network quality classification (QoS) and allows users to export results as CSV for further analysis.
🚀 Features
- 📥 Download speed measurement  
- 📤 Upload speed measurement  
- 📡 Ping test using HTTP requests  
- 🔌 TCP latency measurement (multi-port testing)  
- 🌍 User location detection (GPS-based)  
- 📶 Network type detection (WiFi / Mobile / Ethernet / etc.)  
- 📊 QoS classification:
  - 🏅 Excellent
  - ✅ Good
  - ⚠️ Fair
  - ❌ Poor  
- 🕓 Test history tracking  
- 💾 Export results to CSV file  
- 📤 Share CSV via WhatsApp / Email  
- 🎨 Clean blue-themed UI with real-time updates  
 🧠 Technical Highlights
This project demonstrates practical implementation of:
- Asynchronous networking in Flutter (HTTP + Socket connections)
- Real-time state management using StatefulWidget
- Internet speed measurement using external API integration
- Custom latency measurement algorithms (HTTP + TCP)
- Device location handling with permission management
- Network state detection using connectivity services
- Local file storage and CSV generation
- Cross-platform sharing functionality

🛠️ Tech Stack
- Flutter (Dart)
- flutter_internet_speed_test
- http
- geolocator
- connectivity_plus
- permission_handler
- path_provider
- csv
- share_plus
- open_file
 App Overview
ProxyNetTest measures network performance in real-world conditions:

- Speed test uses multi-phase download/upload measurement
- Ping is calculated using HTTP HEAD requests
- Latency is measured using TCP socket connection timing
- Results are averaged over multiple attempts for accuracy

📊 QoS (Quality of Service) Logic

Network quality is categorized based on:

- Download speed (Mbps)
- Upload speed (Mbps)
- Ping latency (ms)

 Classification Rules:
- 🏅 EXCELLENT: High speed + low latency
- ✅ GOOD: Stable broadband / 4G
- ⚠️ FAIR: Weak or inconsistent connection
- ❌ POOR: High latency or very low speed


 Data Export

All test results can be:
- Saved locally as a CSV file
- Appended to previous results safely (no overwriting)
- Shared directly via messaging/email apps


